Congenital blindness, porencephaly, and neonatal thrombocytopenia: a report of four cases. Four unrelated infants with neonatal thrombocytopenia associated with congenital blindness and porencephaly have been seen over an 18-year period. The association of congenital blindness with neonatal thrombocytopenia has not previously been reported. All children had clinical purpura in the neonatal period in three cases, thrombocytopenia was confirmed, while in one case, the diagnosis of thrombocytopenia was presumptive